#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Uvod"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Gametype:"
msgstr "Vrsta igre:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Board, Arcade"
msgstr "Tabla, Arkadna"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number of possible players:"
msgstr "Število možnih igralcev:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Four"
msgstr "Štiri"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:72
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kajongg; is a board game created after the famous oriental game of Mah Jong "
"(from Chinese <foreignphrase lang=\"zh\">麻將</foreignphrase>). It is played "
"by four players. Worldwide many different rulesets are in use. Right now "
"&kajongg; supports the Classical Chinese rules as played in Germany, "
"eventually other main rulesets will follow. It is possible to customize or "
"add new rulesets. Please do so and send them to the program author for "
"integration!"
msgstr ""
"&kajongg; je družabna igra, ustvarjena po znani orientalski igri Mah Jong "
"(iz kitajščine <foreignphrase lang=\"zh\">麻將</foreignphrase>). Igrajo jo "
"štirje igralci. Po vsem svetu se uporablja veliko različnih pravil. Trenutno "
"&kajongg; podpira klasična kitajska pravila, kot se igrajo v Nemčiji, "
"sčasoma bodo sledili drugi glavni nizi pravil. Možno je prilagoditi ali "
"dodati nove nabore pravil. Prosimo, da to storite in jih pošljete avtorju "
"programa v integracijo!"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kajongg; can be used in two different ways: Scoring a manual game where you "
"play as always without the help of a computer and use &kajongg; for the "
"computation of scores and for bookkeeping. Or you can use &kajongg; to play "
"against any combination of other human players or computer players."
msgstr ""
"&kajongg; se lahko uporablja na dva različna načina: točkovanje ročne igre, "
"kjer kot vedno igrate brez pomoči računalnika in uporabljate &kajongg; za "
"izračun rezultatov in za knjigovodstvo. Lahko pa uporabite &kajongg; za "
"igranje proti kateri koli kombinaciji drugih človeških igralcev ali "
"računalniških igralcev."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Screen Layout"
msgstr "Postavitev zaslona"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:84 index.docbook:162 index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "A screenshot of &kajongg;"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona &kajongg;"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:89 index.docbook:166 index.docbook:227 index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot"
msgstr "Posnetek zaslona"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "A quick explanation of the parts of the game screen."
msgstr "Hitra razlaga delov igralnega zaslona."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:98
#, no-c-format
msgid "Toolbar"
msgstr "Orodna vrstica"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Toolbar is located beneath the menubar and contains buttons for the most "
"often used actions. The content of the Toolbar can be edited. You can also "
"make it invisible, giving more room to the Board."
msgstr ""
"Orodna vrstica se nahaja pod menijsko vrstico in vsebuje gumbe za "
"najpogosteje uporabljena dejanja. Vsebino orodne vrstice je mogoče urejati. "
"Prav tako jo lahko naredite nevidno in s tem zagotovite več prostora za "
"tablo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the size of your screen you may want to make the toolbar "
"invisible or to move it to the left side of the window. You can do that by "
"click with the &RMB; on the toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Odvisno od velikosti vašega zaslona boste morda želeli orodno vrstico "
"narediti nevidno ali jo premakniti na levo stran okna. To lahko storite "
"tako, da kliknete &RMB; na orodni vrstici."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "Board"
msgstr "Tabla"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Board is the largest section of the window. You see the four walls with "
"a length of 18 tiles (the exact number depends on the rules like using bonus "
"tiles or not). The names of the players are written on the walls, together "
"with the current value of the hand (as far as known) and their wind tiles. "
"The prevailing wind has a coloured background, east in the screenshot above."
msgstr ""
"Tabla je največji del okna. Vidite štiri stene z dolžino 18 ploščic (točno "
"število je odvisno od pravil, kot je uporaba bonus ploščic ali ne). Imena "
"igralcev so napisana na stenah, skupaj s trenutno vrednostjo kombinacije (če "
"je znano) in njihovimi ploščicami vetra. Prevladujoči veter ima barvno "
"ozadje, vzhod na zgornjem posnetku zaslona."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When <link linkend=\"play\">playing</link>, the interior of the walls holds "
"the tiles discarded by the players. They are randomly placed. The last "
"discarded tile has a blue focus frame."
msgstr ""
"Med <link linkend=\"play\">igranjem</link> so v notranjosti sten ploščice, "
"ki so jih igralci odvrgli. Postavljeni so naključno. Zadnja zavržena "
"ploščica ima moder fokusni okvir."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When <link linkend=\"scoreGame\">scoring manual games</link>, the interior "
"of the walls has a selection of all available tiles, the central selector. "
"You can assign them to the players using the mouse or the keyboard."
msgstr ""
"Pri <link linkend=\"scoreGame\">točkovanju ročnih iger</link> ima notranjost "
"sten izbor vseh razpoložljivih ploščic, osrednji izbirnik. Igralcem jih "
"lahko dodelite z miško ali s tipkovnico."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid "Player Region"
msgstr "Regija igralca"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:119
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Every player has a screen range for her tiles. The upper row contains "
"exposed tiles, the lower row concealed tiles. When <link linkend=\"scoreGame"
"\">scoring manual games</link>, concealed tiles are shown with a shadow over "
"the entire tile. Bonus tiles go to the right end."
msgstr ""
"Vsak igralec ima razpon zaslona za svoje ploščice. Zgornja vrsta vsebuje "
"vidne ploščice, spodnja vrstica skrite ploščice. Pri <link linkend="
"\"scoreGame\">točkovanju ročnih iger</link> so skrite ploščice prikazane s "
"senco čez celotno ploščico. Bonus ploščice gredo na desni konec."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dialog"
msgstr "Dialog"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog presents choices the player has. Most often it has a timeout with "
"a progress bar showing the remaining time."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno predstavlja izbire, ki jih ima igralec. Najpogosteje ima "
"časovno omejitev z vrstico napredka, ki prikazuje preostali čas."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:132
#, no-c-format
msgid "Status bar"
msgstr "Statusna vrstica"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Status bar is located at the bottom of the screen and contains the "
"current totals for the players."
msgstr ""
"Statusna vrstica se nahaja na dnu zaslona in vsebuje trenutne skupne "
"vrednosti za igralce."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scoring a Manual Game"
msgstr "Točkovanje ročne igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this mode, &kajongg; is only used to do the scoring. You play as usual "
"with real people on a real table and at the end of a game you can tell "
"&kajongg; the tiles a player has in her hand and everything else &kajongg; "
"needs to know for calculating the scores - which is what the program will "
"do. Alternatively you can calculate the hand scores manually and enter them. "
"&kajongg; will then make the payments amongst the players and write the "
"results into a data base. It is possible to suspend a game, start another "
"game with other players and resume old games. All rules will be saved "
"together with the games, so different games can be played with different "
"rules."
msgstr ""
"V tem načinu se &kajongg; uporablja samo za točkovanje. Igrate kot običajno "
"z resničnimi ljudmi na resnični mizi in na koncu igre lahko rečete &kajongg; "
"ploščice, ki jih ima igralec v roki in vse ostalo &kajongg; mora vedeti za "
"izračun rezultatov - kar bo program tudi naredil. Lahko pa ročno izračunate "
"rezultate rok in jih vnesete. &kajongg; bo nato izvedel plačila med igralci "
"in zapisal rezultate v bazo podatkov. Možno je prekiniti igro, začeti novo "
"igro z drugimi igralci in nadaljevati stare igre. Vsa pravila bodo shranjena "
"skupaj z igrami, tako da lahko različne igre igrate z različnimi pravili."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:145
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the menu, select <menuchoice><guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Score "
"Manual Game</guimenuitem></menuchoice> or press <keycombo action=\"simul"
"\">&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo>."
msgstr ""
"V meniju izberite <menuchoice><guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Ročno "
"izračunaj igro</guimenuitem></menuchoice> ali pritisnite <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap> </keycombo>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can either select an existing unfinished game or start a new game. "
"If you start a new game, you will be asked for the players and the ruleset. "
"&kajongg; will propose the same values used for the previous game. If there "
"was no previous game, it will propose the first four defined players. Please "
"note that you cannot change the ruleset or any of its rules after this "
"selection. You can do that beforehand in <link linkend=\"ruleset-options"
"\">the ruleset editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj lahko izberete obstoječo nedokončano igro ali začnete novo igro. Če "
"začnete novo igro, boste morali vnesti igralce in nabor pravil. &kajongg; bo "
"predlagal enake vrednosti, kot so bile uporabljene v prejšnji igri. Če ni "
"bilo prejšnje igre, bo predlagal prve štiri določene igralce. Upoštevajte, "
"da po tej izbiri ne morete spremeniti nabora pravil ali katerega koli od "
"njegovih pravil. To lahko storite vnaprej v <link linkend=\"ruleset-options"
"\">urejevalniku nabora pravil</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you get a new window titled <guilabel>Scoring for this Hand</guilabel>. "
"Read <link linkend=\"enterhand-tiles\">Have &kajongg; compute the score</"
"link> for a detailed description."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj dobite novo okno z naslovom <guilabel>Točkovanje za to roko</guilabel>. "
"Preberite <link linkend=\"enterhand-tiles\">Naj &kajongg; izračuna rezultat</"
"link> za podroben opis."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "After saving hand results, continue with the next hand."
msgstr "Ko shranite rezultate roke, nadaljujte z naslednjo roko."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "Entering hand results"
msgstr "Vnos rezultatov rok"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scores"
msgstr "Rezultati"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the window for entering hand results. It automatically shows itself "
"when &kajongg; thinks you might need it. You can always show or hide it by "
"pressing <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> or "
"by selecting the corresponding menu entry."
msgstr ""
"To je okno za vnos rezultatov rok. Samodejno se prikaže, ko &kajongg; misli, "
"da bi ga morda potreboval. Vedno ga lahko prikažete ali skrijete s pritiskom "
"<keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>S</keycap></keycombo> ali z izbiro "
"ustreznega menijskega vnosa."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "As always the prevailing wind has its background colored."
msgstr "Kot vedno ima prevladujoči veter obarvano ozadje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here you can manually enter scores for all players. Alternatively you can "
"exactly define which tiles a player had in her hand. If you choose to do "
"that, the corresponding field for the manual score value will be grayed out. "
"&kajongg; will automatically compute the score."
msgstr ""
"Tukaj lahko ročno vnesete rezultate za vse igralce. Druga možnost je, da "
"lahko natančno določite, katere ploščice je imel igralec v njegovi roki. Če "
"se odločite za to, bo ustrezno polje za ročno vrednost rezultata zatemnjeno. "
"&kajongg; bo samodejno izračunal rezultat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having entered all relevant data for a hand, press the button "
"<guibutton>Save Hand</guibutton>. The hand values will be entered in the "
"data base, and they are also shown in the score table. You might be prompted "
"to change the seating positions of the players but you can choose not to "
"change seats. The proposed changes are currently not customizable - if a "
"ruleset needs something different, we will change that."
msgstr ""
"Ko vnesete vse ustrezne podatke za roko, pritisnite gumb <guibutton>Shrani "
"roko</guibutton>. Vrednosti rok bodo vnesene v bazo podatkov, prikazane pa "
"bodo tudi v tabeli rezultatov. Morda boste pozvani, da spremenite položaje "
"igralcev, vendar se lahko odločite, da ne zamenjate sedežev. Predlaganih "
"sprememb trenutno ni mogoče prilagoditi – če nabor pravil potrebuje nekaj "
"drugačnega, bomo to spremenili."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the player might have won, the check box in the column <guilabel>Winner</"
"guilabel> will be enabled - click this for the winner."
msgstr ""
"Če je igralec morda zmagal, bo potrditveno polje v stolpcu "
"<guilabel>Zmagovalec</guilabel> omogočeno - kliknite to za zmagovalca."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:184
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The status bar will now show the updated balances for the players, and you "
"can continue with the next hand."
msgstr ""
"Vrstica stanja bo zdaj prikazala posodobljena stanja za igralce in lahko "
"nadaljujete z naslednjo roko."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enter the score manually"
msgstr "Vnesite rezultat ročno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A good player will probably prefer to compute her score himself. In that "
"case you can directly enter it. This is only possible when no tiles are "
"selected for this player."
msgstr ""
"Dober igralec bo verjetno raje sam izračunal njen rezultat. V tem primeru ga "
"lahko neposredno vnesete. To je mogoče le, če za tega igralca ni izbrana "
"nobena ploščica."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:192
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you enter a manual score, it must already contain everything except "
"penalties, you will have no optional rules to choose from. There is one "
"exception: <quote>Dangerous Game</quote>. This does not influence any "
"scores, it is no offense either. It only means the payment between players "
"is different: The offender pays all for all to the winner. The other two "
"players do not exchange payments. This is currently not customizable."
msgstr ""
"Če vnesete ročni rezultat, mora že vsebovati vse razen kazni, ne boste imeli "
"izbirnih pravil med katerimi lahko izbirate. Obstaja ena izjema: "
"<quote>Nevarna igra</quote>. To ne vpliva na ocene, tudi ni žalitev. To le "
"pomeni, da je plačilo med igralci različno: storilec plača vse za vse "
"zmagovalcu. Druga dva igralca ne izmenjujeta plačil. Tega trenutno ni mogoče "
"prilagoditi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "Have &kajongg; compute the score"
msgstr "Naj &kajongg; izračuna rezultat"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you explicitly tell &kajongg; what tiles a player holds, entering scores "
"will be grayed out for that player in this window. While associating tiles "
"with a player you will see how her score will grow - but as soon as you add "
"the 14th tile the score goes to zero. That might surprise you but unless you "
"declare this as the winner hand, it is recognized as a long hand which "
"always has zero points. This behaviour is defined by the Classical Chinese "
"ruleset, it might be different if you change the rules or use a different "
"ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Če izrecno poveste &kajongg; katere ploščice ima igralec, bo vnos rezultatov "
"za tega igralca v tem oknu zatemnjen. Med povezovanjem ploščic z igralcem "
"boste videli, kako bo njegov rezultat rasel - toda takoj, ko dodate 14. "
"ploščico, gre rezultat na nič. To bi vas lahko presenetilo, vendar če tega "
"ne razglasite za zmagovalno kombinacijo, je priznana kot dolga kombinacija, "
"ki ima vedno nič točk. To vedenje je opredeljeno s klasičnim kitajskim "
"naborom pravil, morda je drugače, če spremenite pravila ali uporabite drug "
"nabor pravil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:201
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can associate tiles and melds with a player using either the mouse or "
"the keyboard or both. With the mouse simply move tiles by dragging/dropping "
"them to the player region. When dropping the tile, you will be asked what "
"you want to move: Single, Pair, Pung, Kong, Claimed Kong or Chow. The upper "
"row is for exposed tiles, the lower row for concealed tiles. The bonus tiles "
"will appear to the far right. You can also move tiles and melds between "
"rows, between players and back to the central selector."
msgstr ""
"Ploščice in zlitja lahko povežete z igralcem z uporabo miške ali tipkovnice "
"ali obojega. Z miško preprosto premaknite ploščice tako, da jih povlečete/"
"spustite v območje igralca. Ko spustite ploščico, boste pozvani, kaj želite "
"premakniti: eno, par, pung, kong, zahtevani kong ali čov. Zgornja vrsta je "
"za vidne ploščice, spodnja vrsta za skrite ploščice. Bonus ploščice se bodo "
"prikazale skrajno desno. Prav tako lahko premikate ploščice in kombinacije "
"med vrsticami, med igralci in nazaj do osrednjega izbirnika."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you prefer using the keyboard, you can use &Tab; to move between the "
"central selector and the player regions. The keys <keycap>eswnESWN</keycap> "
"move a tile to the players East, South, West and North. The keys <keycap>xX</"
"keycap> move it back to the central selector. <keycap>ESWN</keycap> moves to "
"the concealed row, <keycap>eswn</keycap> moves to the exposed row. You can "
"move the cursor between tiles or melds using the arrow keys, the currently "
"selected tile or meld has a blue frame. Since the key arrows are far away "
"from letters on the keyboard, you can also use the letters <keycap>hjkl</"
"keycap> or <keycap>HJKL</keycap> for moving the cursor. <keycap>hH</keycap> "
"move left, <keycap>jJ</keycap> move down, <keycap>kK</keycap> move up, "
"<keycap>lL</keycap> move right. This is how the unix editor <command>vi</"
"command> does it. The &kde; browser &konqueror; and even this help program "
"also support those keys in the same way. Those keys may differ if you use a "
"language other than English but it is currently not possible to configure "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Če raje uporabljate tipkovnico, lahko uporabite &Tab; za premikanje med "
"osrednjim selektorjem in regijami igralcev. Tipke <keycap>eswnESWN</keycap> "
"premaknejo ploščico do igralcev vzhod, jug, zahod in sever. Tipke "
"<keycap>xX</keycap> ga premaknejo nazaj na osrednji izbirnik. <keycap>ESWN</"
"keycap> premakne v skrito vrstico, <keycap>eswn</keycap> premakne v vidno "
"vrstico. Kazalec lahko premikate med ploščicami ali združitvami s puščičnimi "
"tipkami, trenutno izbrana ploščica ali združitev ima moder okvir. Ker so "
"puščice na tipkah daleč stran od črk na tipkovnici, lahko za premikanje "
"kazalca uporabite tudi črki <keycap>hjkl</keycap> ali <keycap>HJKL</keycap>. "
"<keycap>hH</keycap> pomik levo, <keycap>jJ</keycap> pomik navzdol, "
"<keycap>kK</keycap> pomik navzgor, <keycap>lL</keycap> pomik desno. Tako to "
"počne urejevalnik Unix <command>vi</command>. &kde; brskalnik &konqueror; in "
"tudi ta program za pomoč podpira te tipke na enak način. Te tipke se lahko "
"razlikujejo, če uporabljate jezik, ki ni angleščina, vendar jih trenutno ni "
"mogoče konfigurirati."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The options <guilabel>Last Tile:</guilabel> and <guilabel>Last Meld:</"
"guilabel> are needed by some rules like <guilabel>Last tile completes pair</"
"guilabel>. They can only be used for the winner hand."
msgstr ""
"Možnosti <guilabel>Zadnja ploščica:</guilabel> in <guilabel>Zadnje zlitje:</"
"guilabel> potrebujeta nekatera pravila, kot je <guilabel>Zadnja ploščica "
"zaključi par</guilabel>. Uporabljajo se lahko le za zmagovalno roko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:214
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the right part of the window you can manually apply some rules. What "
"rules appear in this list depends on the current ruleset and on the tiles. "
"In the example of the above screen shot, the losing players might have an "
"option <quote>dangerous game</quote> - again depending on the ruleset and on "
"their tiles. It is the aim of the developers to keep this list of manually "
"selectable rules as short as possible. Optimally &kajongg; should always be "
"able to automatically determine whether a rule applies, but sometimes "
"&kajongg; does not have enough information or knowledge to decide."
msgstr ""
"V desnem delu okna lahko ročno uporabite nekatera pravila. Katera pravila so "
"prikazana na tem seznamu, je odvisno od trenutnega nabora pravil in ploščic. "
"V primeru zgornjega posnetka zaslona imajo lahko poraženi igralci možnost "
"<quote>Nevarna igra</quote> – spet odvisno od nabora pravil in njihovih "
"ploščic. Cilj razvijalcev je, da je ta seznam ročno izbranih pravil čim "
"krajši. Optimalno &kajongg; vedno mora biti sposoben samodejno ugotoviti, "
"ali velja pravilo, vendar včasih &kajongg; nima dovolj informacij ali znanja "
"za odločitev."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "Penalties"
msgstr "Kazni"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"enterhand\">window for entering hand results</link>, "
"the <guibutton>Penalties</guibutton> button will bring up this window where "
"you can enter penalties. This can be done at any point in time independent "
"of the normal scoring mechanism."
msgstr ""
"V <link linkend=\"enterhand\">oknu za vnos rezultatov kombinacij</link> bo "
"gumb <guibutton>Kazni</guibutton> prikazal to okno, kjer lahko vnesete "
"kazni. To je mogoče storiti kadar koli, neodvisno od običajnega mehanizma "
"točkovanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Offense:</guilabel> selection shows all offenses that might be "
"applicable to the hands the players hold. Choose among them."
msgstr ""
"Izbira <guilabel>Napad:</guilabel> prikazuje vse prekrške, ki bi lahko "
"veljali za roke, ki jih držijo igralci. Izberite med njimi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now you can adapt the <guilabel>Total Penalty</guilabel>. This is the total "
"sum that is moved from payers to payees. It will be evenly split between "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj lahko prilagodite <guilabel>Skupno kazen</guilabel>. To je skupni "
"znesek, ki se premakne od plačnikov k prejemnikom plačil. Enakomerno bo "
"razdeljen mednje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the type of offense, the number of payers and payees varies. "
"The right number of players is displayed. If you select a player, &kajongg; "
"ensures that this player only occurs once by adapting the other players."
msgstr ""
"Glede na vrsto prekrška se število plačnikov in prejemnikov plačil "
"razlikuje. Prikaže se pravo število igralcev. Če izberete igralca, &kajongg; "
"zagotavlja, da se ta igralec pojavi samo enkrat s prilagajanjem drugih "
"igralcev."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "Playing"
msgstr "Igranje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At any time, you can enable or disable the Demo Mode. In Demo Mode, the "
"computer will play for you. If no game is currently played, a new game will "
"be started with the last used ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Kadarkoli lahko omogočite ali onemogočite demo način. V demo načinu bo "
"računalnik igral namesto vas. Če se trenutno ne igra nobena igra, se začne "
"nova igra z zadnjim uporabljenim naborom pravil."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "Play against the computer"
msgstr "Igrajte proti računalniku"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First you will get a login dialog. Enter the game server you want to connect "
"to and your user name. If you choose the special entry <guilabel>Local Game</"
"guilabel>, you only need to enter your name (or accept the proposed name) "
"and the wanted ruleset. This will immediately start a local game where you "
"play against 3 robot players. However if suspended games exist, they will be "
"displayed in a list. You can then select the game you want to continue with "
"or start a new game."
msgstr ""
"Najprej boste dobili pogovorno okno za prijavo. Vnesite strežnik igre, s "
"katerim se želite povezati, in svoje uporabniško ime. Če izberete poseben "
"vnos <guilabel>Lokalna igra</guilabel>, morate vnesti samo svoje ime (ali "
"sprejeti predlagano ime) in želeni nabor pravil. To bo takoj začelo lokalno "
"igro, v kateri igrate proti trem robotskim igralcem. Če pa obstajajo "
"suspendirane igre, bodo prikazane na seznamu. Nato lahko izberete igro, s "
"katero želite nadaljevati, ali začnete novo igro."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Play with friends"
msgstr "Igrajte se s prijatelji"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to play against other real people, you need a game server to "
"which all players, including yourself, need to connect. Do that by selecting "
"any other host or by manually entering a new host name and by specifying "
"your password for that host. The last used password will be proposed."
msgstr ""
"Če želite igrati proti drugim resničnim ljudem, potrebujete strežnik za "
"igre, na katerega se morajo povezati vsi igralci vključno z vami. To storite "
"tako, da izberete katerega koli drugega gostitelja ali ročno vnesete novo "
"ime gostitelja in navedete svoje geslo za tega gostitelja. Predlagano bo "
"zadnje uporabljeno geslo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The easiest way is to use the game server at <literal>kajongg.org</literal>. "
"&kajongg; will show this one in the list of possible game servers. Please "
"note that this server only offers a game server but no web page or any other "
"services."
msgstr ""
"Najlažji način je, da uporabite strežnik za igre na <literal>kajongg.org</"
"literal>. &kajongg; bo tega prikazal na seznamu možnih igralnih strežnikov. "
"Upoštevajte, da ta strežnik ponuja le strežnik za igre, ne pa tudi spletne "
"strani ali drugih storitev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:262
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not have an account on the game server with the name you entered, "
"you will be asked if you want to open an account. If you say yes, you will "
"get a new dialog where you can enter the wanted password twice. Your account "
"will be created automatically."
msgstr ""
"Če na igralnem strežniku nimate računa z imenom, ki ste ga vnesli, boste "
"pozvani, ali želite odpreti račun. Če odgovorite pritrdilno, se vam prikaže "
"novo pogovorno okno, kjer lahko dvakrat vnesete želeno geslo. Vaš račun bo "
"ustvarjen samodejno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After a successful login onto the game server, you will get a list of tables "
"with available seats on that game server. Join a table or allocate a new "
"table. If you allocate a new table, wait until more seats are taken by other "
"players. You can start the game on a table you allocated at any time, the "
"seats not taken will be filled by robot players."
msgstr ""
"Po uspešni prijavi v igralni strežnik boste prejeli seznam miz s prostimi "
"sedeži na tem igralnem strežniku. Pridružite se mizi ali dodelite novo mizo. "
"Če dodelite novo mizo, počakajte, da drugi igralci zasedejo več sedežev. "
"Igro lahko kadar koli začnete na mizi, ki ste jo dodelili, nezasedeni sedeži "
"bodo zasedeni z robotskimi igralci."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The table list also shows the name of the ruleset played on that table. The "
"ruleset and its name are sent to the game server by the player initiating "
"the table. If you have an identical ruleset, the table shows your name for "
"the ruleset - this might be helpful if the table initiator speaks another "
"language and named the ruleset differently. Also, if the name of your local "
"ruleset is displayed, it is displayed in black. If however you have no "
"identical ruleset, the name appears in red, and you can use the button "
"<guibutton>Compare</guibutton> to compare it with your own rulesets."
msgstr ""
"Seznam miz prikazuje tudi ime nabora pravil, ki se igra na tej mizi. Nabor "
"pravil in njegovo ime pošlje igralnemu strežniku igralec, ki začne mizo. Če "
"imate identičen nabor pravil, je v tabeli prikazano vaše ime za nabor pravil "
"– to bi lahko bilo v pomoč, če pobudnik tabele govori drug jezik in je nabor "
"pravil poimenoval drugače. Tudi, če je prikazano ime vašega lokalnega nabora "
"pravil, je prikazano v črni barvi. Če pa nimate identičnega nabora pravil, "
"se ime prikaže rdeče in uporabite gumb <guibutton>Primerjaj</guibutton>, da "
"ga primerjate s svojimi nabori pravil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you do not use <literal>kajongg.org</literal> or any other existing game "
"server, you can start your own &kajongg; game server in two different ways:"
msgstr ""
"Če ne uporabljate <literal>kajongg.org</literal> ali katerega koli drugega "
"obstoječega igralnega strežnika, lahko zaženete svoj &kajongg; igralni "
"strežnik na dva različna načina:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"connect to the server <literal>localhost</literal>. This is your own "
"computer. If you do this and no game server is running, it will be started "
"automatically. And when you stop playing, the server will be stopped too. "
"This differs from selecting <guilabel>Local Game</guilabel>, the latter does "
"not allow connections from other computers."
msgstr ""
"povežite se s strežnikom <literal>localhost</literal>. To je vaš računalnik. "
"Če to storite in noben igralni strežnik ne deluje, se bo zagnal samodejno. "
"In ko nehate igrati, bo ustavljen tudi strežnik. To se razlikuje od izbire "
"<guilabel>Lokalna igra</guilabel>, saj slednja ne dovoljuje povezav iz "
"drugih računalnikov."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"manually start a server on any computer you want. All you need to do is go "
"to a command line and start the program <command>kajonggserver</command>. "
"Entering <command>kajonggserver --help</command> will show you all available "
"options like changing the default port. This server will run until you kill "
"it."
msgstr ""
"ročno zaženite strežnik na kateremkoli računalniku, ki ga želite. Vse kar "
"morate storiti je, da greste v ukazno vrstico in zaženete program "
"<command>kajonggserver</command>. Če vnesete <command>kajonggserver --help</"
"command>, se vam bodo prikazale vse razpoložljive možnosti, na primer "
"sprememba privzetih vrat. Ta strežnik bo deloval, dokler ga ne ubijete."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In both cases you need to tell the other players how they can reach your "
"game server. They need the &URL; or simply an IP address and the port your "
"server is listening on. This might be something like <literal>mypc.dyndns."
"org:8301</literal> where <literal>8301</literal> is the port. Of course you "
"need to configure your firewall such that the remote player can reach that "
"port. The communication will be encrypted."
msgstr ""
"V obeh primerih morate drugim igralcem povedati, kako lahko dosežejo vaš "
"igralni strežnik. Potrebujejo &URL; ali preprosto naslov IP in vrata, ki jih "
"vaš strežnik posluša. To je lahko nekaj takega kot <literal>mypc.dyndns."
"org:8301</literal>, kjer so <literal>8301</literal> vrata. Seveda morate "
"vdorobran konfigurirati tako, da lahko oddaljeni predvajalnik doseže ta "
"vrata. Komunikacija bo šifrirana."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:288
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For the port number, please see <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>About &kajongg;</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. The Protocol "
"version is the port number. For &kajongg; 17.04 this is 8301. If the player "
"enters no port for the wanted game server, the client computes the port in "
"the same way. So if a computer runs several game servers with different "
"protocol versions, you should normally reach the correct game server "
"automatically. Anyway the game server and the client will make sure that "
"their versions are compatible and warn you otherwise."
msgstr ""
"Za številko vrat glejte <menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu> <guimenuitem>O "
"&kajongg;</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Različica protokola je številka vrat. "
"Za &kajongg; 17.04 je to 8301. Če igralec ne vnese nobenih vrat za želeni "
"igralni strežnik, odjemalec izračuna vrata na enak način. Torej, če "
"računalnik poganja več igralnih strežnikov z različnimi različicami "
"protokola, bi morali običajno samodejno doseči pravi igralni strežnik. "
"Kakorkoli že, bosta igralni strežnik in odjemalec poskrbela, da sta njuni "
"različici združljivi, in vas opozorila na nasprotno."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you encounter possible bugs, you might want to use the option "
"<command>kajongg --debug=traffic</command>. This will show you, on the "
"console where the game server has been started, what messages are flowing "
"between the game server and the clients. For more options, see "
"<command>kajongg --help</command>"
msgstr ""
"Če naletite na možne napake, boste morda želeli uporabiti možnost "
"<command>kajongg --debug=traffic</command>. To vam bo na konzoli, kjer je "
"bil zagnan igralni strežnik, pokazalo, katera sporočila tečejo med igralnim "
"strežnikom in odjemalci. Za več možnosti glejte <command>kajongg --help</"
"command>"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid "Caveats"
msgstr "Opozorila"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to make sure nobody can cheat none of the human players should "
"have access to the computer the game server is running on. Of course you can "
"never avoid that two players help each other because you cannot know what "
"they really are doing. Two players might even be one and the same person."
msgstr ""
"Če se želite prepričati, da nihče ne more goljufati, nihče od človeških "
"igralcev ne sme imeti dostopa do računalnika, na katerem teče strežnik igre. "
"Seveda se nikoli ne morete izogniti temu, da si dva igralca pomagata, ker ne "
"morete vedeti, kaj v resnici počneta. Dva igralca sta lahko celo ena in ista "
"oseba."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:304
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game rules"
msgstr "Pravila igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Worldwide, many different game variants exist. Currently, &kajongg; supports "
"two variants of Classical Chinese, one as played in Germany and one as "
"played in Great Britain."
msgstr ""
"Po vsem svetu obstaja veliko različnih različic igre. Trenutno &kajongg; "
"podpira dve različici klasične kitajske, eno, kot jo igrajo v Nemčiji, in "
"eno, kot jo igrajo v Veliki Britaniji."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This description does not go into details and as such matches both variants."
msgstr ""
"Ta opis se ne spušča v podrobnosti in kot tak ustreza obema različicama."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "However most of the basic rules are the same in most variants."
msgstr "Vendar je večina osnovnih pravil v večini različic enaka."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:308
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Since the program &kajongg; knows how to play, this description only "
"contains things that might not be obvious."
msgstr ""
"Ker program &kajongg; zna igrati, ta opis vsebuje samo stvari, ki morda niso "
"očitne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:309
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you want to learn Mah Jong in more detail, please consult the <link "
"linkend=\"bibliography\">bibliography</link>."
msgstr ""
"Če se želite Mah Jong naučiti podrobneje, si oglejte <link linkend="
"\"bibliography\">bibliografijo</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "The aim of the game"
msgstr "Cilj igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each player tries to collect tiles such that she has a winning hand. On "
"achieving this, she calls <quote>Mah Jong</quote>. In a winning hand, the "
"tiles are normally grouped into five melds: Four melds with three or four "
"tiles each and a fifth meld consisting of two equal tiles. A normal meld has "
"three or four identical tiles (called Pung and Kong respectively) or three "
"successive tiles like Bamboo 3, Bamboo 4, Bamboo 5 (called Chow)."
msgstr ""
"Vsak igralec poskuša zbrati ploščice tako, da ima zmagovalno roko. Ko to "
"doseže, pokliče <quote>Mah Jong</quote>. V zmagoviti igri so ploščice "
"običajno razvrščene v pet skupin: štiri kombinacije s tremi ali štirimi "
"ploščicami in peta kombinacija, ki je sestavljena iz dveh enakih ploščic. "
"Običajna kombinacija ima tri ali štiri enake ploščice (imenovane Pung "
"oziroma Kong) ali tri zaporedne ploščice, kot so Bambus 3, Bambus 4, Bambus "
"5 (imenovan Čov)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:317
#, no-c-format
msgid "The course of the game"
msgstr "Potek igre"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Initially, the player with the East wind (as indicated on the wall) has one "
"more tile than the other players. East begins by discarding an unwanted tile."
msgstr ""
"Na začetku ima igralec z vzhodnim vetrom (kot je označeno na steni) eno "
"ploščico več kot drugi igralci. Vzhodni začne tako, da zavrže neželeno "
"ploščico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever a tile has been discarded, other players can claim it by saying "
"what they can complete with that tile (Chow, Pung, Kong, Mah Jong). Only the "
"next player can claim a Chow - the other claims are possible for all "
"players. A meld completed by a claim will be exposed - made visible to all "
"players."
msgstr ""
"Kadarkoli je bila ploščica zavržena, jo lahko drugi igralci zahtevajo tako, "
"da povedo, kaj lahko dokončajo s to ploščico (Čov, Pung, Kong, Mah Jong). "
"Samo naslednji igralec lahko zahteva Čov - ostali zahtevki so možni za vse "
"igralce. Zlitje, dokončano z zahtevkom, bo izpostavljeno – vidna vsem "
"igralcem."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:325
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If nobody claims the discarded tile, the next player, South (and then West "
"and North) gets a tile from the wall and discards an unwanted tile."
msgstr ""
"Če nihče ne zahteva zavržene ploščice, naslednji igralec, Jug (in nato Zahod "
"in Sever), dobi ploščico s stene in zavrže neželeno ploščico."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several rules about when a Pung can be extended to a Kong (by "
"claiming the forth tile or by getting it from the wall) - these rules are "
"not explained here. But &kajongg; of course knows them and makes sure they "
"are respected. If a Kong is declared, the player automatically gets a "
"replacement tile from the wall - otherwise it would not be possible to build "
"the five melds as mentioned above."
msgstr ""
"Obstaja več pravil o tem, kdaj je Pung mogoče razširiti na Konga (z "
"prevzemom četrte ploščice ali tako, da jo vzamete iz stene) - ta pravila "
"tukaj niso pojasnjena. Toda &kajongg; seveda jih pozna in skrbi za njihovo "
"spoštovanje. Če je razglašen Kong, igralec samodejno dobi nadomestno "
"ploščico s stene – sicer ne bi bilo mogoče zgraditi petih zlitij, kot je "
"omenjeno zgoraj."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:333
#, no-c-format
msgid "Year, Round and Hand"
msgstr "Leto, krog in roka"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:333
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a player claims Mah Jong or we end up in a draw, a hand is completed. "
"Now, except for draws, the winds rotate among the players. This is repeated "
"until every player once had every wind. This entire unit is called a round. "
"An entire game, also called year, consists of four such rounds: East wind "
"round, South wind round, West wind round, North wind round. The wind of a "
"round is also called prevailing wind, it can result in higher scores."
msgstr ""
"Ko igralec zahteva Mah Jong ali smo na koncu izenačeni, je roka zaključena. "
"Zdaj se, razen remijev, menjajo vetrovi med igralci. To se ponavlja, dokler "
"vsak igralec enkrat ne dobi vsakega vetra. Celotna enota se imenuje krog. "
"Celotna igra, imenovana tudi leto, je sestavljena iz štirih takih krogov: "
"krog vzhodnega vetra, krog južnega vetra, krog zahodnega vetra, krog "
"severnega vetra. Veter kroga se imenuje tudi prevladujoči veter, lahko "
"povzroči višje ocene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"So a full game (a year) consists of at least 16 hands. Since the winds do "
"not rotate for draws or when the East player says Mah Jong, a higher number "
"of hands is normally needed for a full game."
msgstr ""
"Torej je celotna igra (leto) sestavljena iz vsaj 16 rok. Ker se vetrovi ne "
"vrtijo za remije ali ko vzhodni igralec reče Mah Jong, je za celotno igro "
"običajno potrebno večje število rok."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "Bonus tiles"
msgstr "Bonus ploščice"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A game can contain eight bonus tiles (unless the rules exclude them). They "
"are exposed separately on the right side of the player region as they are "
"never used for building melds. They do however generate bonus points."
msgstr ""
"Igra lahko vsebuje osem bonus ploščic (razen če jih pravila izključujejo). "
"Izpostavljeni so ločeno na desni strani območja igralca, saj se nikoli ne "
"uporabljajo za gradnjo zlitij. Vendar ustvarjajo bonus točke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:343
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a player gets a bonus tile, she will automatically also get a replacement "
"tile from the wall. And a bell rings."
msgstr ""
"Če igralec dobi bonus ploščico, samodejno dobi tudi nadomestno ploščico s "
"stene. In zazvoni zvonec."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "Scoring"
msgstr "Točkovanje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the end of a hand, the score for each player is computed. First, basis "
"points are counted like 2 points for a simple exposed pung or 20 points for "
"winning. Next, another set of rules is applied - those rules can double the "
"points like one double for a meld of dragons. When the score for each hand "
"is known, differences are paid between players - while the winner gets its "
"full score paid from all other players. East always gets and pays twice her "
"score."
msgstr ""
"Na koncu igre se izračuna rezultat za vsakega igralca. Prvič, osnovne točke "
"se štejejo kot 2 točki za preprosti pung ali 20 točk za zmago. Nato se "
"uporabi še en niz pravil - ta pravila lahko podvojijo točke kot ena dvojna "
"za zlitje zmajev. Ko je rezultat za vsako kombinacijo znan, se razlike "
"izplačajo med igralci – medtem ko zmagovalec prejme svoj celoten rezultat od "
"vseh drugih igralcev. Vzhodni vedno dobi in plača dvakrat svoj rezultat."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Of course &kajongg; knows about all applicable rules but a good player knows "
"what combinations get what score so she can optimize. While learning it is "
"recommended to activate the window <guimenuitem>Explain Scores</guimenuitem>."
msgstr ""
"Seveda &kajongg; pozna vsa veljavna pravila, vendar dober igralec ve, katere "
"kombinacije dobijo kakšen rezultat, tako da lahko optimizira. Med učenjem je "
"priporočljivo aktivirati okno <guimenuitem>Razloži ocene</guimenuitem>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The exact scoring rules often vary - in &kajongg; you are free to change "
"them with the <link linkend=\"ruleset-options\">the ruleset editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Natančna pravila točkovanja se pogosto razlikujejo - v &kajongg; lahko jih "
"spremenite z <link linkend=\"ruleset-options\">urejevalnikom nabora pravil</"
"link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The ruleset editor also shows you all available rules and their meaning. "
"Place the mouse over them and for the more exotic rules help text will "
"appear."
msgstr ""
"Urejevalnik nabora pravil vam pokaže tudi vsa razpoložljiva pravila in "
"njihov pomen. Postavite miško nadnje in za bolj eksotična pravila se bo "
"prikazalo besedilo pomoči."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to play with &kajongg;"
msgstr "Kako igrati z &kajongg;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You will be prompted for what you want to do. This is a little dialog which "
"appears either on the right or at the bottom depending on the size of the "
"window. If you make it broader than high, the dialog appears on the right. "
"Sometimes the dialog will have a timeout - when it is over, the first "
"possible answer is automatically selected for you. This timeout is "
"configurable in the Ruleset Editor, under <guilabel>Options</guilabel>, "
"<guilabel>Claim Timeout</guilabel>. All players should have the same "
"timeout, that is why this is part of the ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Pozvani boste, kaj želite storiti. To je majhno pogovorno okno, ki se "
"prikaže na desni ali na dnu, odvisno od velikosti okna. Če ga naredite "
"širšega od visokega, se pogovorno okno prikaže na desni. Včasih bo pogovorno "
"okno imelo časovno omejitev - ko se konča, se za vas samodejno izbere prvi "
"možni odgovor. Ta časovna omejitev je nastavljiva v urejevalniku nabora "
"pravil pod <guilabel>Možnosti</guilabel>, <guilabel>Časovna omejitev "
"zahtevka</guilabel>. Vsi igralci morajo imeti enako časovno omejitev, zato "
"je to del nabora pravil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need to select a tile from your hand, you can move between tiles "
"using the &Right; and &Left; arrow keys or the letters <keycap>h</keycap> "
"and <keycap>l</keycap> on your keyboard. Of course you can use the mouse too."
msgstr ""
"Če morate izbrati ploščico iz svoje roke, se lahko premikate med ploščicami "
"z &Right; in &Left; puščične tipke ali črke <keycap>h</keycap> in <keycap>l</"
"keycap> na tipkovnici. Seveda lahko uporabite tudi miško."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can discard a tile by using the keyboard the same way as for all "
"actions. Alternatively, you can use the mouse and move the tile from your "
"hand into the discard area (the interior of the walls). The placement of the "
"tile in the discard area will still be done by the computer - because the "
"placement should be the same for players."
msgstr ""
"Ploščico lahko zavržete z uporabo tipkovnice na enak način kot za vsa "
"dejanja. Druga možnost je, da uporabite miško in premaknete ploščico iz "
"svoje roke v območje za odmet (notranjost sten). Postavitev ploščice v "
"območje za odmet bo še vedno opravil računalnik - ker mora biti postavitev "
"enaka za igralce."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often, the dialogs will offer choices which are not really applicable like "
"calling Pung when you do not have the needed tiles. This is intended - just "
"like in a real game. But you can configure impossible choices away: Disable "
"<guilabel>Show only possible actions</guilabel> on the <guilabel>Play</"
"guilabel> page of the settings dialog."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorna okna pogosto ponujajo izbire, ki v resnici niso uporabne, na "
"primer klic Pung, ko nimate potrebnih ploščic. To je namenjeno - tako kot v "
"pravi igri. Lahko pa konfigurirate nemogoče izbire: onemogočite "
"<guilabel>Pokaži samo možna dejanja</guilabel> na strani "
"<guilabel>Predvajaj</guilabel> pogovornega okna z nastavitvami."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Discarded tiles are placed randomly between the walls. Some game variants "
"define where the tiles should be placed, this is not yet configurable "
"however. When it becomes configurable, it will be part of the ruleset."
msgstr ""
"Zavržene ploščice so naključno postavljene med stene. Nekatere različice "
"igre določajo, kje naj bodo ploščice postavljene, vendar tega še ni mogoče "
"konfigurirati. Ko ga bo mogoče konfigurirati, bo del nabora pravil."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Interface Overview"
msgstr "Pregled vmesnika"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:382
#, no-c-format
msgid "Menu Items"
msgstr "Elementi menija"

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Score Manual Game</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>C</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Ročna igra rezultatov</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid "Only score a manually played game."
msgstr "Zadenite samo ročno odigrano igro."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can load an old game or start a new game. By default only pending (&ie; "
"unfinished) games are shown in the selection list. You can optionally show "
"all games including finished games. Here you can also delete games."
msgstr ""
"Lahko naložite staro igro ali začnete novo igro. Privzeto so na izbirnem "
"seznamu prikazane samo čakajoče (tj. nedokončane) igre. Po želji lahko "
"prikažete vse igre, vključno s končanimi igrami. Tukaj lahko tudi izbrišete "
"igre."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Play</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>N</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Igraj</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:399
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Play with others (people and computers)</action>."
msgstr "<action>Igrajte se z drugimi (ljudmi in računalniki)</action>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Abort Game</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>W</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Prekini igro</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Abort the current game. If it was a manual game with scoring only, you can "
"resume it later. If you played using &kajongg;, the game is not yet "
"resumable."
msgstr ""
"Prekini trenutno igro. Če je šlo za ročno igro samo z točkovanjem, jo lahko "
"nadaljujete pozneje. Če ste igrali s &kajongg;, igre še ni mogoče "
"nadaljevati."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:410
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Game</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Quit &kajongg;</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>Q</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Igra</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Zapri &kajongg;</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:415
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Quits</action> &kajongg;."
msgstr "<action>Zapusti</action> &kajongg;."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>H</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Chat</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>H</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Pogled</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Klepet</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:423
#, no-c-format
msgid "Chat"
msgstr "Klepetajte"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:425
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Chat Window</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Okno za klepet</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:431
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Chat Window</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Okno za klepet</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid "Lets you chat with the other players."
msgstr "Omogoča vam klepet z drugimi igralci."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:440
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>T</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Score Table</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>T</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Pogled</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Tabela rezultatov</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:445
#, no-c-format
msgid "<action>Score Table</action>"
msgstr "<action>Tabela rezultatov</action>"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:447 index.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Score Table</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Tabela rezultatov</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Show the score table. Round/Hand are the current round (East, South, West, "
"North) followed by a count of the hands played in that round. The winner has "
"a green background for her values. The Payments show how much the player "
"paid to or received from all other players with this hand. The Balance shows "
"the current balance for all players. The Chart shows the development of the "
"balance values. The hints give you more details: They show all rules that "
"have been applied to this hand. Just move the mouse over the value you are "
"interested in."
msgstr ""
"Pokaži tabelo rezultatov. Round/Hand je trenutni krog (vzhod, jug, zahod, "
"sever), ki mu sledi štetje odigranih rok v tem krogu. Zmagovalec ima zeleno "
"ozadje za svoje vrednote. Plačila prikazujejo, koliko je igralec plačal ali "
"prejel od vseh drugih igralcev s to roko. Stanje prikazuje trenutno stanje "
"za vse igralce. Graf prikazuje razvoj bilančnih vrednosti. Namigi vam dajo "
"več podrobnosti: prikazujejo vsa pravila, ki so bila uporabljena za to roko. "
"Samo premaknite miško nad vrednost, ki vas zanima."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:463
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The lower part shows the used ruleset. Between the score table and the used "
"ruleset you can find a splitter letting you change the relative sizes of "
"both parts."
msgstr ""
"Spodnji del prikazuje uporabljeni nabor pravil. Med tabelo rezultatov in "
"uporabljenim naborom pravil najdete razdelilnik, ki vam omogoča spreminjanje "
"relativne velikosti obeh delov."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>E</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Explain Scores</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>E</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Pogled</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Razloži rezultate</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid "Explain Scores"
msgstr "Razloži rezultate"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:481
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Score Table</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Tabela rezultatov</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:485
#, no-c-format
msgid "Explains how the score for the current hand was computed."
msgstr "Pojasnjuje, kako je bil izračunan rezultat za trenutno roko."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>F</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Full Screen Mode</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;&Shift;<keycap>F</keycap></"
"keycombo></shortcut> <guimenu>Pogled</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Celozaslonski "
"način</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:495
#, no-c-format
msgid "Switches between full screen mode and normal mode."
msgstr "Preklaplja med celozaslonskim in običajnim načinom."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:499
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Players</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Igralci</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:503
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add, modify and delete players."
msgstr "Dodajanje, spreminjanje in brisanje igralcev."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:504
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The passwords in this table are those used by default when logging onto a "
"game server. Changing the password you initially chose for a game server is "
"not yet really helpful because there is no way yet for you to also change "
"your password on the game server. You would have to ask the administrator of "
"the game server to do that for you directly in the data base."
msgstr ""
"Gesla v tej tabeli so tista, ki se privzeto uporabljajo pri prijavi v "
"igralni strežnik. Spreminjanje gesla, ki ste ga prvotno izbrali za igralni "
"strežnik, še ni v veliko pomoč, ker še ni možnosti, da bi spremenili geslo "
"tudi na igralnem strežniku. Morali bi prositi skrbnika igralnega strežnika, "
"da to stori namesto vas neposredno v bazi podatkov."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Rulesets</guimenuitem>"
msgstr "<guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Nabori pravil</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:515
#, no-c-format
msgid "Customize rulesets."
msgstr "Prilagodite nabore pravil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the Ruleset Editor to customize rulesets. For details see <link linkend="
"\"ruleset-options\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"Uporabite urejevalnik nabora pravil za prilagajanje nabora pravil. Za "
"podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"ruleset-options\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:519
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>G</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Change Visual Angle</"
"guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>G</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Spremeni vidni kot</"
"guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid "Changes the viewing angle of the tiles counterclockwise."
msgstr "Spremeni kot gledanja ploščic v nasprotni smeri urinega kazalca."

#. Tag: menuchoice
#: index.docbook:527
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>D</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Demo Mode</guimenuitem>"
msgstr ""
"<shortcut><keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>D</keycap></keycombo></"
"shortcut> <guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Demo način</guimenuitem>"

#. Tag: action
#: index.docbook:532
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enables or disables the Demo Mode. See <link linkend=\"play\">here</link> "
"for details."
msgstr ""
"Omogoči ali onemogoči demo način. Za podrobnosti glejte <link linkend=\"play"
"\">tukaj</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:536
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Additionally &kajongg; has the common &kde; <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> and "
"<guimenu>Help</guimenu> menu items, for more information read the sections "
"about the <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings"
"\">Settings Menu</ulink> and <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus."
"html#menus-help\">Help Menu</ulink> of the &kde; Fundamentals."
msgstr ""
"Poleg tega &kajongg; ima skupno &kde; Elementi menija <guimenu>Nastavitve</"
"guimenu> in <guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu>, za več informacij preberite razdelke o "
"<ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-settings\">meniju z "
"nastavitvami</ulink> in <ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/menus.html#menus-help"
"\">meni Pomoč</ulink> v &kde; Osnove."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Configuration"
msgstr "Konfiguracija igre"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:548
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screeninfo>Configure Dialog</screeninfo>"
msgstr "<screeninfo>Pogovorno okno za konfiguracijo</screeninfo>"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid "<phrase>Configure Dialog</phrase>"
msgstr "<phrase>Pogovorno okno za konfiguracijo</phrase>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:559
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The menu entry <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Configure &kajongg;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> opens the "
"<guilabel>Configure - &kajongg;</guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""
"Vnos menija <menuchoice><guimenu>Nastavitve</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Konfiguriraj &kajongg;...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> odpre "
"pogovorno okno <guilabel>Konfiguriraj - &kajongg;</guilabel>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:560
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you press the <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> button here, all of your "
"configuration changes will be reverted, including everything you did with "
"the ruleset editor."
msgstr ""
"Če tukaj pritisnete gumb <guibutton>Prekliči</guibutton>, bodo vse vaše "
"spremembe konfiguracije razveljavljene, vključno z vsem, kar ste naredili z "
"urejevalnikom nabora pravil."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:561
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can also select the different tabs with the keyboard: <keycombo action="
"\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo> selects the first tab "
"<guilabel>Play</guilabel> options, <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Ctrl;"
"<keycap>2</keycap></keycombo> selects the second tab, and so on."
msgstr ""
"S tipkovnico lahko izberete tudi različne zavihke: <keycombo action=\"simul"
"\">&Ctrl;<keycap>1</keycap></keycombo> izbere prvi zavihek možnosti "
"<guilabel>Predvajaj</guilabel>, <keycombo action =\"simul\">&Ctrl;<keycap>2</"
"keycap></keycombo> izbere drugi zavihek itd."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "Play options"
msgstr "Možnosti igranja"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:571
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show tile shadows"
msgstr "Prikaži sence ploščic"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:573
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This shows tiles with borders and shadows. Also there is some space between "
"tile rows, and the wall tiles are shown such that you can see that the wall "
"is two or three tiles high. So if you disable this option, you have a "
"simpler display with slightly larger tiles. This may be helpful for small "
"screens."
msgstr ""
"To prikazuje ploščice z obrobami in sencami. Med vrstami ploščic je tudi "
"nekaj prostora, stenske ploščice pa so prikazane tako, da lahko vidite, da "
"je stena visoka dve ali tri ploščice. Če torej onemogočite to možnost, imate "
"enostavnejši zaslon z nekoliko večjimi ploščicami. To je lahko koristno za "
"majhne zaslone."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rearrange undisclosed tiles to melds"
msgstr "Prerazporedite nerazkrite ploščice v zlitja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:583
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This groups melds in the hand. Sometimes the grouping might not be like you "
"want it, so you might prefer to have no grouping at all, just like in a real "
"world game."
msgstr ""
"Ta skupina se zlije v roki. Včasih združevanje morda ni takšno, kot bi si ga "
"želeli, zato bi morda raje, da ga sploh ne bi imeli, tako kot v igri tudi v "
"resničnem svetu."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "Show only possible actions"
msgstr "Prikaži samo možna dejanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:592
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When playing, show only possible actions like <quote>No claim</quote> or "
"<quote>Pung</quote>."
msgstr ""
"Med igranjem prikaži samo možna dejanja, kot je <quote>Brez zahtevka</quote> "
"ali <quote>Pung</quote>."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:598
#, no-c-format
msgid "Propose what to do"
msgstr "Predlagajte, kaj narediti"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:600
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Whenever you have a choice of actions like claiming a tile or not or like "
"choosing which tile to discard, &kajongg; can help you by making a proposal."
msgstr ""
"Kadarkoli imate možnost izbire med dejanji, na primer zahtevati ploščico ali "
"ne ali izbrati katero ploščico želite zavreči, &kajongg; vam lahko pomaga s "
"predlogom."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "Use sounds if available"
msgstr "Uporabite zvoke, če so na voljo"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:608
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This lets you hear discards and claims. If other players recorded sound "
"files with their own voice, you can hear them."
msgstr ""
"To vam omogoča, da slišite zavržene in zahtevke. Če so drugi igralci posneli "
"zvočne datoteke s svojim glasom, jih lahko slišite."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "Let others hear my voice"
msgstr "Naj drugi slišijo moj glas"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:616
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you recorded sound files with your voice this option will let the other "
"players hear your discards and claims with your voice."
msgstr ""
"Če ste zvočne datoteke posneli z glasom, bo ta možnost drugim igralcem "
"omogočila, da z vašim glasom slišijo vaše zavržke in zahtevke."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "Animation speed:"
msgstr "Hitrost animacije:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define how fast the tiles should move around. If you move the slider to the "
"rightmost position, tile movement is not animated: the tiles will simply "
"change place."
msgstr ""
"Določite, kako hitro naj se ploščice premikajo. Če premaknete drsnik na "
"skrajni desni položaj, premikanje ploščice ni animirano: ploščice bodo "
"preprosto zamenjale mesto."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:632
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sound"
msgstr "Zvok"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Playing gives you a much nicer experience if you hear players claim tiles "
"and announce discards. It also makes playing easier because you can "
"concentrate on your own tiles, you do not have to watch what others discard."
msgstr ""
"Igranje vam daje veliko lepšo izkušnjo, če slišite igralce, ki zahtevajo "
"ploščice in napovedujejo zavržene. Prav tako olajša igranje, ker se lahko "
"osredotočite na svoje ploščice, ni vam treba gledati, kaj drugi zavržejo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:637
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kajongg; comes with voices for different players. It automatically assigns "
"voices to players. For every language there should be four voices, "
"preferably two male and two female. &kajongg; tries to use voices in the "
"same language &kajongg; runs in. If it finds no voices in that language, "
"&kajongg; will fallback to other languages, using the same fallback "
"languages you defined for &kajongg; (see <menuchoice><guimenu>Help</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Switch Application Language</guimenuitem></menuchoice>). If no "
"voice files exist yet for your language, you are invited to record and "
"contribute them to &kajongg;."
msgstr ""
"&kajongg; prihaja z glasovi za različne igralce. Igralcem samodejno dodeli "
"glasove. Za vsak jezik naj bodo štirje glasovi, po možnosti dva moška in dva "
"ženska. &kajongg; poskuša uporabiti glasove v istem jeziku &kajongg; steče. "
"Če ne najde glasov v tem jeziku, &kajongg; se bo vrnil v druge jezike z "
"uporabo istih nadomestnih jezikov, ki ste jih določili za &kajongg; (glejte "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Pomoč</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Preklop jezika aplikacije</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>). Če za vaš jezik še ni govornih datotek, vas "
"vabimo, da jih posnamete in prispevate v &kajongg;."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is how you can generate voices yourself. There is a separate folder for "
"every voice. Please note that those folders may be somewhere else on your "
"system, they depend on how &kde; was installed. Only the part starting with "
"<filename class=\"directory\">kajongg</filename> is always the same. There "
"are two groups of voices with different places in the file system:"
msgstr ""
"Tako lahko sami ustvarite glasove. Za vsak glas obstaja posebna mapa. "
"Upoštevajte, da so te mape lahko nekje drugje v vašem sistemu, odvisno od "
"tega, kako &kde; je bil nameščen. Samo del, ki se začne z <filename class="
"\"directory\">kajongg</filename>, je vedno enak. Obstajata dve skupini "
"glasov z različnimi mesti v datotečnem sistemu:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Predefined voices for every language. They live in a folder like <filename "
"class=\"directory\">/usr/share/kajongg/voices/LANG</filename> where LANG is "
"the code for your language. The voice directories directly under <filename "
"class=\"directory\">.../kajongg/voices/</filename> are the US-english "
"versions. Predefined voices are randomly assigned to players. Those voices "
"have names like <quote><literal>male1 male2 female1 female2</literal></"
"quote> but those names do not matter, the user will never see them."
msgstr ""
"Prednastavljeni glasovi za vsak jezik. Živijo v mapi, kot je <filename class="
"\"directory\">/usr/share/kajongg/voices/LANG</filename>, kjer je LANG koda "
"za vaš jezik. Glasovni imeniki neposredno pod <filename class=\"directory"
"\">.../kajongg/voices/</filename> so ameriško-angleške različice. Vnaprej "
"določeni glasovi so naključno dodeljeni igralcem. Ti glasovi imajo imena, "
"kot je <quote><literal>male1 male2 female1 female2</literal></quote>, vendar "
"ta imena niso pomembna, uporabnik jih ne bo nikoli videl."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:654
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"User voices can be defined for a specific user. If &kajongg; makes use of "
"such a voice, it can automatically be transferred to other players over the "
"internet. Those voices live in a folder like <filename class=\"directory"
"\">~/.local/share/apps/kajongg/voices/</filename>. So if your login name is "
"joe, this might be <filename class=\"directory\">/home/joe/.local/share/apps/"
"kajongg/voices/joe/</filename>. The folder <filename class=\"directory"
"\">voices/</filename> might not yet exist - if so, create it."
msgstr ""
"Uporabniške glasove je mogoče določiti za določenega uporabnika. Če "
"&kajongg; uporablja takšen glas, se lahko samodejno prenese na druge igralce "
"prek interneta. Ti glasovi živijo v mapi, kot je <filename class=\"directory"
"\">~/.local/share/apps/kajongg/voices/</filename>. Torej, če je vaše "
"prijavno ime joe, je to morda <filename class=\"directory\">/home/joe/.local/"
"share/apps/kajongg/voices/joe/</filename>. Mapa <filename class=\"directory"
"\">voices/</filename> morda še ne obstaja - če obstaja, jo ustvarite."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now that you know where to place your new voice, generate a new folder for "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Zdaj, ko veste, kam postaviti svoj novi glas, ustvarite novo mapo zanj."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:664
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In that subfolder, you can place the sound files. They have to be encoded "
"with the <ulink url=\"https://xiph.org/vorbis/\">Ogg Vorbis</ulink> audio "
"compressor, the file names need to have the extension <filename class="
"\"extension\">.ogg</filename>. A single file has a name like <filename>s3."
"ogg</filename> - this is Stone 3. You should define such files for all tiles "
"and for all claims and announcements. But if a sound file is missing, "
"nothing bad happens - you just will not hear that sound. Fallback to other "
"voices or languages only works for entire voices, not for single sound files."
msgstr ""
"V to podmapo lahko postavite zvočne datoteke. Morajo biti kodirane z zvočnim "
"kompresorjem <ulink url=\"https://xiph.org/vorbis/\">Ogg Vorbis</ulink>, "
"imena datotek morajo imeti pripono <filename class=\"extension\">. ogg</"
"filename>. Posamezna datoteka ima ime, kot je <filename>s3.ogg</filename> - "
"to je Stone 3. Takšne datoteke bi morali definirati za vse ploščice ter za "
"vse zahtevke in objave. Če pa zvočna datoteka manjka, se ne zgodi nič hudega "
"- tega zvoka preprosto ne boste slišali. Povratek na druge glasove ali "
"jezike deluje samo za celotne glasove, ne pa za posamezne zvočne datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:670
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After having defined all sound files for a predefined voice, please make "
"sure that the &kajongg; process has write permission in the new voice "
"folder. Start &kajongg; and test the voice. After everything is OK, you can "
"revoke write permission (and you should do so for predefined voices). "
"&kajongg; will automatically generate a file named <filename>md5sum</"
"filename> containing a checksum over all sound files. Whenever you change, "
"add or delete a sound file for a voice, &kajongg; will try to rewrite that "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Ko definirate vse zvočne datoteke za vnaprej določen glas, se prepričajte, "
"da ima &kajongg; proces dovoljenje za pisanje v novo glasovno mapo. Zaženite "
"&kajongg; in preizkusite glas. Ko je vse v redu, lahko prekličete dovoljenje "
"za pisanje (in to morate storiti za vnaprej določene glasove). &kajongg; "
"samodejno ustvari datoteko z imenom <filename>md5sum</filename>, ki vsebuje "
"kontrolno vsoto vseh zvočnih datotek. Kadarkoli spremenite, dodate ali "
"izbrišete zvočno datoteko za glas, bo &kajongg; poskusil znova napisati to "
"datoteko."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:676
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please make the length of the sound short but speak clearly - this game can "
"be played very fast when you get used to it. It is easier if you first write "
"down a list with everything that should be spoken. Do not read it as a "
"sequence of items, try to pronounce each item as if it were the only one and "
"as you would when playing. Leave room between the items. Reading this needs "
"a little practicing."
msgstr ""
"Prosim, naj bo zvok kratek, vendar govorite jasno - to igro lahko igrate "
"zelo hitro, ko se je navadite. Lažje je, če si najprej napišete seznam z "
"vsem, kar je treba povedati. Ne berite ga kot zaporedja elementov, poskusite "
"vsak element izgovoriti, kot da je edini in tako kot bi med igranjem. "
"Pustite prostor med predmeti. Branje tega zahteva malo vaje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "This is just one possibility to create the sound files:"
msgstr "To je samo ena možnost za ustvarjanje zvočnih datotek:"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:682
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Record a sound file with the program <command>qarecord</command>, save it in "
"the <acronym>WAV</acronym> format. In this single sound file, speak all of "
"the sounds."
msgstr ""
"Posnemite zvočno datoteko s programom <command>qarecord</command> in jo "
"shranite v formatu <acronym>WAV</acronym>. V tej eni zvočni datoteki "
"izgovorite vse zvoke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Edit that file with the sound editor <command>audacity</command>. In that "
"editor, use the mouse to mark a range of the sound waves. The editor will "
"play that part. Repeat until you have the correct part selected. This may be "
"easier if you <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Zoom In</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Use the menu command <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu> <guimenuitem>Export Selection</guimenuitem></menuchoice> and save "
"in the <filename class=\"extension\">.ogg</filename> format. Under "
"<guilabel>Options</guilabel>, choose low quality - this is sufficient and "
"even wanted because this reduces the time to transfer the sounds to the "
"other players."
msgstr ""
"Uredite to datoteko z urejevalnikom zvoka <command>audacity</command>. V tem "
"urejevalniku z miško označite obseg zvočnih valov. To vlogo bo odigral "
"urednik. Ponavljajte, dokler ne izberete pravega dela. To je morda lažje, če "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Ogled</guimenu> <guimenuitem>Povečaj</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>. Uporabite menijski ukaz <menuchoice><guimenu>Datoteka</guimenu> "
"<guimenuitem>Izvozi izbor</guimenuitem></menuchoice> in shranite v formatu "
"<filename class=\"extension\">.ogg</filename>. Pod <guilabel>Možnosti</"
"guilabel> izberite nizko kakovost - to zadostuje in je celo zaželeno, ker "
"skrajša čas za prenos zvokov na druge predvajalnike."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:693
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following are the names of the files that you should generate. Always "
"append <filename class=\"extension\">.ogg</filename> to them:"
msgstr ""
"Sledijo imena datotek, ki jih morate ustvariti. Vedno jim pripnite <filename "
"class=\"extension\">.ogg</filename>:"

